  <h2>Our Mission</h2>
  <p>Happy Pet Advice was created with a simple idea: pet owners deserve clear, honest information about the animals they love. Not clinical textbook language. Not fear-inducing medical jargon. Just straightforward, warm, and genuinely helpful content that makes your life with your pet better.</p>
  <p>We focus specifically on dogs and cats — the two most beloved companion animals in the United States. Our articles cover everything from understanding your pet's behavior and emotions to recognizing health symptoms early, managing everyday challenges, and choosing products that actually work.</p>

  <h2>Who We Write For</h2>
  <p>Our primary audience is dog and cat owners who care deeply about their pets — people who see their animals not just as pets, but as true members of the family. We write for people who want practical guidance they can act on right away, not overwhelming information that leaves more questions than answers.</p>

  <h2>What We Cover</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Dog and cat behavior</strong> — understanding what your pet is communicating and why they do what they do</li>
    <li><strong>Health and wellness</strong> — recognizing symptoms, knowing when to worry, and how to support your pet's wellbeing</li>
    <li><strong>Emotional connection</strong> — the science and reality behind the bond between pets and their owners</li>
    <li><strong>Product guidance</strong> — honest reviews and recommendations for food, beds, treatments, and more</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>A Note About Veterinary Advice</h2>
  <div class="about-highlight">
    Happy Pet Advice is an informational resource, not a substitute for professional veterinary care. If your pet is showing symptoms of illness, pain, or behavioral distress, please consult a licensed veterinarian.
  </div>

  <h2>Our Values</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Honesty first.</strong> We only publish content we believe to be accurate and helpful.</li>
    <li><strong>Simplicity over jargon.</strong> Pet care information should be accessible to everyone.</li>
    <li><strong>Compassion in every word.</strong> We understand the love you feel for your animal is real and profound.</li>
    <li><strong>No sensationalism.</strong> Our goal is to inform and reassure, not to cause panic.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Get in Touch</h2>
  <p>We'd love to hear from you. Reach out through our <a href="/contact/">Contact page</a>. Every message is read by a real person.</p>

